methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setCallerInfo(@NonNull CallerInfo callerInfo)
methods.comment: * @param callerInfo the CallerInfo object to get the target contact from.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setNumber(@NonNull String number)
methods.comment: * @param number the phone number to be added to the calls db

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setPostDialDigits(@NonNull String postDialDigits)
methods.comment:
* @param postDialDigits the post-dial digits that were dialed after the number,
             *        if it was outgoing. Otherwise it is ''.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setViaNumber(@NonNull String viaNumber)
methods.comment:
* @param viaNumber the secondary number that the incoming call received with. If the
             *        call was received with the SIM assigned number, then this field must be ''.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setPresentation(int presentation)
methods.comment:
* @param presentation enum value from TelecomManager.PRESENTATION_xxx, which
             *        is set by the network and denotes the number presenting rules for
             *        "allowed", "payphone", "restricted" or "unknown"

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setCallType(int callType)
methods.comment: * @param callType enumerated values for "incoming", "outgoing", or "missed"

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setFeatures(int features)
methods.comment: * @param features features of the call (e.g. Video).

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setAccountHandle(@NonNull PhoneAccountHandle accountHandle)
methods.comment: * @param accountHandle The accountHandle object identifying the provider of the call

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setStart(long start)
methods.comment: * @param start time stamp for the call in milliseconds

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setDuration(int duration)
methods.comment: * @param duration call duration in seconds

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setDataUsage(long dataUsage)
methods.comment:
* @param dataUsage data usage for the call in bytes or
             *                  {@link Long#MIN_VALUE} if data usage was not tracked
             *                  for the call.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setAddForAllUsers(boolean addForAllUsers)
methods.comment:
* @param addForAllUsers If true, the call is added to the call log of all currently
             *        running users. The caller must have the MANAGE_USERS permission if this is
             *        true.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setUserToBeInsertedTo(@NonNull UserHandle userToBeInsertedTo)
methods.comment:
* @param userToBeInsertedTo {@link UserHandle} of user that the call is going to be
             *                           inserted to. null if it is inserted to the current user.
             *                           The value is ignored if {@link #setAddForAllUsers} is
             *                           called with {@code true}.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setIsRead(boolean isRead)
methods.comment:
* @param isRead Flag to show if the missed call log has been read by the user or not.
             *                Used for call log restore of missed calls.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setCallBlockReason(int callBlockReason)
methods.comment: * @param callBlockReason The reason why the call is blocked.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setCallScreeningAppName(@NonNull CharSequence callScreeningAppName)
methods.comment: * @param callScreeningAppName The call screening application name which block the call.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setCallScreeningComponentName(@NonNull String callScreeningComponentName)
methods.comment:
* @param callScreeningComponentName The call screening component name which blocked
             *                                   the call.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setMissedReason(long missedReason)
methods.comment: * @param missedReason The encoded missed information of the call.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setPriority(int priority)
methods.comment:
* @param priority The priority of the call, either {@link Calls#PRIORITY_NORMAL}
             *                 or {@link Calls#PRIORITY_URGENT} as sent via call composer

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setSubject(@NonNull String subject)
methods.comment: * @param subject The subject as sent via call composer.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setLatitude(double latitude)
methods.comment: * @param latitude Latitude of the location sent via call composer.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setLongitude(double longitude)
methods.comment: * @param longitude Longitude of the location sent via call composer.

methods.name: public AddCallParametersBuilder setPictureUri(@NonNull Uri pictureUri)
methods.comment:
* @param pictureUri {@link Uri} returned from {@link #storeCallComposerPicture}.
             *                   Associates that stored picture with this call in the log.

methods.comment: * @param isPhoneAccountMigrationPending whether the phone account migration is pending

methods.comment: * @param isBusinessCall should be set if the caller is a business call

methods.comment:
